The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, April 2: Rahul Gandhi has become one of the trustees of the Jawahar Bhavan Trust. The trust will also have two other new members  AICC treasurer Motilal Vora and Union minister Mukul Wasnik.           
	Vora has been made the secretary of the trust in place of Ahmed Patel, who will continue to be a trustee. The reshuffle, one of the many philanthropic outfits associated with the Nehru-Gandhi family, takes place after every three years.                   
	 Vadodara (PTI): A man set his girlfriend on fire at Motafofalia village in Uttar Pradesh on Thursday. Dinesh Vasava had learnt that Nirus parents were getting her married. The victim was rushed to the hospital where she was declared dead. Her parents have lodged a complaint against the man,who is missing.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): A 25-year-old woman arrested in a cheating case allegedly committed suicide in a Goregaon police station on Friday. She was found hanging from a ceiling fan in the room where she had been kept for questioning.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Air India pilots have warned of legal action if the management does not stop recruiting trainee pilots, saying that the existing cockpit crew is under-utilised. The Indian Commercial Pilots Association has complained in a letter to Air India that even the average flying hours for pilots have dropped from 90 to 60 hours per month.                  
	 Kalpetta (PTI): A gram panchayat in Keralas Wayanad district has come out with a scheme to provide social security to senior citizens by providing less strenuous jobs under the Mahatma Gandhi National Rural Employment Guarantee Scheme.                  
	 Lucknow (PTI): Four poachers were arrested and a leopard skin was seized from them in Lakhimpur Kheri in Uttar Pradesh on Friday, police said.                                                                                                                                              
